	<article id="post-142" class="post-142 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-strategy-and-hints">
		<header class="entry-header">
						<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="../medium-8.html" rel="bookmark">Medium &#8211; 8</a></h1>
			
						<div class="entry-meta">
				<span class="sep">Posted on </span><a href="../medium-8.html" title="5:11 pm" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2017-07-03T17:11:00+00:00">July 3, 2017</time></a><span class="by-author"> <span class="sep"> by </span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="../author/star-scythe_8.html" title="View all posts by Silent Zebra" rel="author">Silent Zebra</a></span></span>			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
			
						<div class="comments-link">
				<a href="../medium-8.html#respond"><span class="leave-reply">Reply</span></a>			</div>
					</header><!-- .entry-header -->

				<div class="entry-content">
			<p>The hardest part of this level is the beginning. The key is to recognize that this is the position you want to continue from:</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="alignnone size-large wp-image-219" src="../wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170703-130847-576x1024.png" alt="" width="576" height="1024" srcset="http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170703-130847-576x1024.png 576w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170703-130847-169x300.png 169w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170703-130847-768x1365.png 768w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170703-130847.png 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 576px) 100vw, 576px" /></p>
<p>The only other potentially tricky piece is recognizing the <a href="../general-strategy-ends.html">end</a> (which is the top left corner of the I).</p>
					</div><!-- .entry-content -->
		
