	</article><!-- #post-131 -->

				
					
	<article id="post-205" class="post-205 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-strategy-and-hints">
		<header class="entry-header">
						<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="../general-strategy-rules-thumb.html" rel="bookmark">General Strategy &#8211; Rules of Thumb</a></h1>
			
						<div class="entry-meta">
				<span class="sep">Posted on </span><a href="../general-strategy-rules-thumb.html" title="3:06 pm" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2017-07-03T15:06:36+00:00">July 3, 2017</time></a><span class="by-author"> <span class="sep"> by </span> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="../author/star-scythe_8.html" title="View all posts by Silent Zebra" rel="author">Silent Zebra</a></span></span>			</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
			
						<div class="comments-link">
				<a href="../general-strategy-rules-thumb.html#respond"><span class="leave-reply">Reply</span></a>			</div>
					</header><!-- .entry-header -->

				<div class="entry-content">
			<p>This section is more applicable for time trials where speed is paramount, and the levels are generally a bit less tricky, but these are good rules of thumb anyway. Unlike the &#8220;do not create 2 ends&#8221; rule, these are not always correct.</p>
<h1>Work Outside -&gt; In</h1>
<p>The general idea here is that when you have a big blob of tiles, the easiest way to avoid getting stuck is by doing circles around the edges first, then working towards the centre.</p>
<p>A related idea is to keep things as round (or square) as possible, and have just one blob of tiles. This is an aesthetically pleasing and easy-to-follow way to reduce the chance of creating extra ends, and otherwise identify problem areas where you may be forced to create an end.</p>
<h1>Clear Red Tiles First</h1>
<p>When I see big blotches of red, I like to go only red first, unless it conflicts with the general idea above to work outside -&gt; in. The idea is that by removing red tiles, you simplify the situation, making it easier to see what you should do next.</p>
<p>Be careful with this general idea, and try to keep it localized. Always prioritize the first rule of thumb, working from the outside in and keeping round/square shapes. Personally, I like to combine the two, where I clear all the red tiles along the outside first, work outside -&gt; in, then clear the next set of outer red tiles, rinse and repeat.</p>
<p>Below is an example putting these rules of thumb into work, on a random level:</p>
<div id="attachment_194" style="width: 586px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-194" decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="wp-image-194 size-large" src="../wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155401-576x1024.png" alt="" width="576" height="1024" srcset="http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155401-576x1024.png 576w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155401-169x300.png 169w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155401-768x1365.png 768w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155401.png 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 576px) 100vw, 576px" /><p id="caption-attachment-194" class="wp-caption-text">Hypothetical starting position</p></div>
<div id="attachment_195" style="width: 586px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-195" decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="wp-image-195 size-large" src="../wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155426-576x1024.png" alt="" width="576" height="1024" srcset="http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155426-576x1024.png 576w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155426-169x300.png 169w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155426-768x1365.png 768w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155426.png 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 576px) 100vw, 576px" /><p id="caption-attachment-195" class="wp-caption-text">Red tiles first, and only on the outside first</p></div>
<div id="attachment_196" style="width: 586px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-196" decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="wp-image-196 size-large" src="../wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155449-576x1024.png" alt="" width="576" height="1024" srcset="http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155449-576x1024.png 576w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155449-169x300.png 169w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155449-768x1365.png 768w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155449.png 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 576px) 100vw, 576px" /><p id="caption-attachment-196" class="wp-caption-text">Clearing more red tiles and on the outside (L shape of yellow tiles and the 6 red tiles box cleared)</p></div>
<div id="attachment_197" style="width: 586px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-197" decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="wp-image-197 size-large" src="../wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155457-576x1024.png" alt="" width="576" height="1024" srcset="http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155457-576x1024.png 576w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155457-169x300.png 169w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155457-768x1365.png 768w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155457.png 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 576px) 100vw, 576px" /><p id="caption-attachment-197" class="wp-caption-text">Note: this move is a bit tricky. I had to move down (shown here) in order to avoid creating extra ends</p></div>
<div id="attachment_198" style="width: 586px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-198" decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="wp-image-198 size-large" src="../wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155513-576x1024.png" alt="" width="576" height="1024" srcset="http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155513-576x1024.png 576w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155513-169x300.png 169w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155513-768x1365.png 768w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155513.png 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 576px) 100vw, 576px" /><p id="caption-attachment-198" class="wp-caption-text">More working around the outside &#8211; I make sure to clear the red tile at the bottom first, as it can be problematic later. At this point, I have kept things tidy and won&#8217;t really be liable to being tricked and getting stuck anymore</p></div>
<div id="attachment_199" style="width: 586px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-199" decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="wp-image-199 size-large" src="../wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155525-576x1024.png" alt="" width="576" height="1024" srcset="http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155525-576x1024.png 576w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155525-169x300.png 169w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155525-768x1365.png 768w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155525.png 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 576px) 100vw, 576px" /><p id="caption-attachment-199" class="wp-caption-text">Continuing on the outside and clearing red tiles&#8230;</p></div>
<div id="attachment_200" style="width: 586px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img aria-describedby="caption-attachment-200" decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="wp-image-200 size-large" src="../wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155537-576x1024.png" alt="" width="576" height="1024" srcset="http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155537-576x1024.png 576w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155537-169x300.png 169w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155537-768x1365.png 768w, http://silentzebra.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/Screenshot_20170701-155537.png 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 576px) 100vw, 576px" /><p id="caption-attachment-200" class="wp-caption-text">And in a relatively clean and simple way, we can finish the level!</p></div>
<p><a href="../strategy-and-hints.html">Back to Strategy and Hints</a></p>
